legacy.full_text: #ChinaNationalDay China railways expects to move a whooping 127M passengers over the next ten-day national holiday starting today across the country, media reports indicate. The day marks 72 years since the People's Liberation Army victory in October 1949.@FangYi85320692

127M passengers is equivalent to about 9% of the total population in China. Chinese people have a seven-day holiday for the National Day. It is a time to commemorate the fallen heroes, to celebrate the achievements of the country and to spend quality time with families.😄

Today is a great day to me! It’s #ChineseNationalDay 🇨🇳 and #InternationalCoffeeDay ☕️

I ❤️ coffee, and I ❤️ China more!

Now that I am in Kampala, I must have a cup of Ugandan🇺🇬 coffee to celebrate😄 https://t.co/Z2KCgwyPCV
